ADDITIONAL TERMS FOR FINANCIAL SERVICES USE

This software is designed for educational and demonstration purposes in credit 
portfolio analytics and risk management. While the methodologies and algorithms 
implemented are based on industry best practices, users are responsible for:

1. Ensuring compliance with applicable financial regulations (Basel III, IFRS9, 
   GDPR, etc.) in their jurisdiction

2. Validating all risk models and calculations before use in production 
   environments

3. Implementing appropriate data governance, security, and privacy controls

4. Conducting thorough testing and validation before deployment in live systems

5. Obtaining necessary regulatory approvals for risk management systems

The authors and contributors make no representations or warranties regarding 
the accuracy, completeness, or suitability of this software for specific 
regulatory or business requirements.

===============================================================================

DISCLAIMER FOR SIMULATED DATA

This project uses synthetic/simulated financial data generated through 
statistical modeling and random number generation. This data:

- Does not represent any real customers, accounts, or financial institutions
- Is created solely for demonstration and educational purposes  
- Should not be used for actual credit decisions or regulatory reporting
- May not reflect real-world distributions or correlations accurately
- Is not subject to data protection regulations as it contains no personal data

Users implementing this system with real customer data are responsible for 
ensuring compliance with all applicable data protection and privacy laws.

